/-
  Audit/KFCausalSetRelationalChiralitySelection.lean

  A RELATIONAL SOURCE FOR THE MICROSCOPIC CHIRAL SIGN

  The complete harmonic causal-growth law still carries a binary chirality
  argument.  This file connects that argument to the independently constructed
  cubic relational pseudoscalar

      Xi = Im Tr(H₁ [H₂,H₃]) / 8.

  For nonzero Xi, the convention

      b(Xi) = -i sign(Xi)

  selects the microscopic quarter turn.  Equivalently, the reflection-odd
  source `h = -Xi` gives the endpoint energy

      E_Xi(y) = Xi y,

  whose unique minimizer on `|y| <= 1/2` is `y = -sign(Xi)/2`.  This agrees
  exactly with the previously derived cubic-chirality projectors.  Reflection
  sends `Xi` to `-Xi`, conjugates the phase, swaps the endpoint kernel, and
  preserves the combined source energy.

  This closes the finite algebraic sign bridge.  It does not prove that a
  preferred nonzero relational triple is generated by the microscopic growth
  dynamics, that the triple is refinement invariant, or that an infinite
  history spontaneously selects one of the reflected sectors.  At `Xi = 0`
  the energy is identically zero and no sign is selected.
-/

